Breath sounds decreased bilaterally; no dry or moist rales or pleural friction rub heard;  
Apical impulse located 1.0 cm lateral to the left midclavicular line in the 5th intercostal space; heart rate 50 beats/min, regular rhythm; heart sounds low; P2 < A2; a grade 2/6 systolic murmur heard in the mitral area;  
Abdomen soft; no painful expression on palpation for tenderness or rebound tenderness; no muscular guarding; no gastric outline or intestinal outline and no peristaltic waves; liver and spleen not palpable below the costal margins;  
No edema of both lower limbs; increased muscle tone in the extremities; muscle strength examination not cooperative; bilateral pathological signs not elicited.

## Initial Examinations
2022.6.1  
