During hospitalization, the patient developed multiple arrhythmias: atrial tachycardia, atrial rhythm  
**List of abnormal items:**  
1. Atrial tachycardia (≥3 consecutive atrial ectopic beats, rate >100 beats/min, abnormal P-wave morphology)  
2. Premature atrial contractions (premature P waves with morphology different from sinus P waves; incomplete compensatory pause)  
3. Atrial arrhythmia (variable P-wave morphologies, irregular RR intervals)

